    {
      "id": "ml81k5gb",
      "questionNumber": 1,
      "questionText": "<p>CORRECT order of stability for the following is \n<br/><br/>$\\mathrm{CH}_2=\\mathrm{CH}^{-}, \\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{CH}_2^{-}, \\mathrm{CH} \\equiv \\mathrm{C}^{-}$</p>\n",
      "options": [
        "<p>$\\mathrm{CH} \\equiv \\mathrm{C}^{-}>\\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{CH}_2^{-}>\\mathrm{CH}_2=\\mathrm{CH}^{-}$</p>\n",
        "<p>$\\mathrm{CH}_2=\\mathrm{CH}^{-}>\\mathrm{CH} \\equiv \\mathrm{C}^{-}>\\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{CH}_2^{-}$</p>\n",
        "<p>$\\mathrm{CH} \\equiv \\mathrm{C}^{-}>\\mathrm{CH}_2=\\mathrm{CH}^{-}>\\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{CH}_2^{-}$</p>\n",
        "<p>$\\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{CH}_2^{-}>\\mathrm{CH}_2=\\mathrm{CH}^{-}>\\mathrm{CH} \\equiv \\mathrm{C}^{-}$</p>"
      ],
      "correctOption": 2,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "stability-of-intermediate",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "<p>Stability of carbanions depends mainly on how well the carbon can hold the negative charge.</p>\n<h3>Step 1: Use NCERT idea — effect of hybridisation (electronegativity)</h3>\n<p>Greater $s$-character $\\Rightarrow$ carbon is more electronegative $\\Rightarrow$ negative charge is more stable.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><p>$sp$ carbon: $50\\%$ $s$-character (most electronegative)</p></li>\n<li><p>$sp^2$ carbon: $33\\%$ $s$-character</p></li>\n<li><p>$sp^3$ carbon: $25\\%$ $s$-character (least electronegative)</p></li>\n</ul>\n<p>So stability order due to hybridisation is:</p>\n<p>$$sp > sp^2 > sp^3$$</p>\n<h3>Step 2: Apply to given carbanions</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><p>$\\mathrm{CH}\\equiv\\mathrm{C}^-$ is on an $sp$ carbon $\\Rightarrow$ most stable  </p></li>\n<li><p>$\\mathrm{CH}_2=\\mathrm{CH}^-$ is on an $sp^2$ carbon $\\Rightarrow$ next  </p></li>\n<li><p>$\\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{CH}_2^-$ is on an $sp^3$ carbon, and also has $+I$ effect of $\\mathrm{CH}_3$ which <strong>destabilises</strong> the negative charge $\\Rightarrow$ least stable</p></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Correct order</h3>\n<p>$$\\mathrm{CH}\\equiv\\mathrm{C}^- \\;>\\; \\mathrm{CH}_2=\\mathrm{CH}^- \\;>\\; \\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{CH}_2^-$$</p>\n<p><strong>Correct option: C</strong></p>",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
